{{Infobox person | name = Christer Ericsson | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = Jan Christer Ericsson | birth_date = {{Birth date|1942|3|27|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Skövde]], Sweden | disappeared_date = {{disappeared date and age|2016|6|28|1942|3|27|df=yes}} | disappeared_place = Outside [[Marstrand]], Sweden | disappeared_status = Found deceased | death_date = {{Death date and age|2016|6|28|1942|3|27|df=yes}} | death_place = Sea outside Marstrand | death_cause = [[Drowning]] | body_discovered = 27 August 2016 | nationality = Swedish | occupation = Businessman }}
'''Jan Christer Ericsson''' (27 March 1942 – 28 June 2016) was a [[Sweden|Swedish]] businessman. He developed a method for loading of containers, in which he tried unsuccessfully to interest his then-bosses at Stena Line.<ref name="expressen.se">{{cite web|url=http://www.expressen.se/gt/sa-blev-christer-ericsson-miljardar/|title=Så blev Christer Ericsson miljardär|language=Swedish|publisher=expressen.se|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref> In his own business, Container Safe J C Ericsson AB, later known as Consafe, he developed his own ideas and was initially successful in [[Ship transport|sea transportation]].<ref name="expressen.se"/> In 1987, he published a book entitled ''Utan omsvep: mitt berikande liv med Consafe''.<!-- A link is found under the Bibliography headline -->
In the late 1970s, Consafe started to manufacture houses and service platforms for offshore businesses in co-operation with Svenska Varv. The business expanded, but went into [[bankruptcy]] in 1985.<ref name="expressen.se"/>
Ericsson had already, before the bankruptcy, started to invest in other businesses. He was a major shareholder in the car dealership Philipson Bil and also invested in the oil and gas industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.upstreamonline.com/live/1442384/ex-prosafe-investor-found-dead|title=Ex-Prosafe investor 'found dead' |last=Marshall |first=Steve |publisher=|accessdate=30 August 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161003145912/http://www.upstreamonline.com/live/1442384/ex-prosafe-investor-found-dead|archivedate=May 18, 2017}}</ref> Ericsson presented an episode of the [[Sveriges Radio]] show ''[[Sommar (radio program)|Sommar i P1]]'' on the 6 July 2006,<ref name="aftonbladet.se">{{cite web|url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/nyheter/article23082193.ab|title=Svensk miljardär saknad till havs|publisher=aftonbladet.se|language=Swedish|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref> where he spoke about his life and business career.<ref name="aftonbladet.se"/>
==Disappearance== Ericsson was reported missing at sea on 28 June 2016. His unoccupied boat had been found with fishing equipment inside it the previous day, north of Marstrand. His body was reportedly found on 27 August.<ref name="thelocal.se">{{cite web|url=http://www.thelocal.se/20160828/missing-swedish-billionaire-found-dead-at-sea|title=Missing Swedish billionaire found dead|date=28 August 2016|publisher=thelocal.se|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/nyheter/article23418818.ab|title=Saknad svensk miljardär hittad död|publisher=aftonbladet.se|language=Swedish|accessdate=30 August 2016}}</ref> At the time of his disappearance and death he was a billionaire in [[Swedish krona|kronor]].<ref name="thelocal.se"/>
